        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agent): dampen Discord stale thread replies",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add Discord-specific message-tool-only guidance that a mention does not require a visible reply\n- steer stale threads, jokes, lightweight acknowledgements, and low-value chatter toward reaction or silence\n- cover the prompt behavior with system prompt assertions\n\n## Diagnosis\nThis was not a Twilio delivery bug. In a Discord thread where final assistant text is private, the runtime correctly exposed `message(action=send)` as the visible reply path. The agent prompt did not make the channel-noise tradeoff explicit enough, so a mention in an old thread got treated as reason to post instead of react/silence.\n\n## Tests\n- `pnpm vitest run src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts` *(blocked: this workspace clone has no `node_modules`; Vitest cannot resolve `vitest/config`)*\n- `git diff --check --cached` before commit",
